So I do work in a company which is called Motion Twin.

39
00:01:42,069 --> 00:01:45,870
We've been talking about that in a previous talk, which

40
00:01:45,910 --> 00:01:46,730
was all about co-op.

41
00:01:47,010 --> 00:01:47,950
So I will just be quick.

42
00:01:48,270 --> 00:01:51,051
We've been making games since 2001.

43
00:01:52,071 --> 00:01:55,952
It was mostly web games, especially web free-to-play

44
00:01:55,972 --> 00:01:57,133
games.

45
00:01:57,393 --> 00:01:59,193
By this time, we were making free-to-play games

46
00:01:59,253 --> 00:02:01,594
was actually cool or not too hard,

47
00:02:01,954 --> 00:02:04,234
because it was before the KPI thing

48
00:02:04,674 --> 00:02:07,275
and the free-to-play aggressive techniques and everything.

49
00:02:07,295 --> 00:02:09,215
It was like the cool free-to-play part.

50
00:02:09,576 --> 00:02:11,499
We also tried to make a few mobile games.

51
00:02:11,579 --> 00:02:12,641
It wasn't that good.

52
00:02:13,161 --> 00:02:15,786
And we actually almost died in the process of doing that.

53
00:02:16,306 --> 00:02:19,912
So we didn't have such a great time on mobile free-to-play.

54
00:02:20,653 --> 00:02:24,019
We should probably have done premium mobile games.

55
00:02:26,127 --> 00:02:30,511
Most people describe us, because it used to be a joke really, like we put that on a website,

56
00:02:30,631 --> 00:02:36,495
it was a Monty Python quote, but most people describe us as being, you know, an anarcho-syndicalist

57
00:02:36,535 --> 00:02:36,815
co-op.

58
00:02:37,336 --> 00:02:38,757
We actually are a co-op.

59
00:02:39,137 --> 00:02:42,660
So it means we, in this company, we are based on three qualities.

60
00:02:43,513 --> 00:02:46,278
The first one is we do work the same amount of time.

61
00:02:46,358 --> 00:02:48,361
So it's eight hours a day, five days a week,

62
00:02:48,822 --> 00:02:49,943
and in the same office.

63
00:02:50,464 --> 00:02:53,008
But that's also because we're a small team that we do that.

64
00:02:53,288 --> 00:02:55,231
It's really important for us to communicate on an everyday

65
00:02:55,271 --> 00:02:55,552
basis.

66
00:02:56,913 --> 00:02:58,934
We also have the exact same decision power.

67
00:02:58,954 --> 00:03:01,876
It's pretty important, because in any kind of decision,

68
00:03:01,956 --> 00:03:04,437
such as a strategic decision, hiring someone,

69
00:03:04,858 --> 00:03:07,499
or deciding if this weapon should be like OP

70
00:03:07,539 --> 00:03:09,481
on the next update, or whatever like that,

71
00:03:09,881 --> 00:03:12,162
everyone can actually take part in the debate.

72
00:03:12,222 --> 00:03:13,623
And if you want to express something,

73
00:03:13,643 --> 00:03:16,505
if you have any kind of idea, anyone can actually vote,

74
00:03:16,905 --> 00:03:21,087
or just talk to anyone to give ideas and to share ideas.

75
00:03:21,748 --> 00:03:24,189
There is always someone in charge at one point,

76
00:03:24,249 --> 00:03:26,370
so to make sure that we don't lose time talking,

77
00:03:26,470 --> 00:03:28,291
because we like talking, but we don't

78
00:03:28,331 --> 00:03:29,672
want that to last forever.

79
00:03:30,252 --> 00:03:31,192
I prefer making games.

80
00:03:32,093 --> 00:03:34,434
Also, the last but really not least,

81
00:03:34,694 --> 00:03:36,115
we are all paid the same way.

82
00:03:36,615 --> 00:03:39,216
So for example, I've been in this company for 18 years.

83
00:03:39,316 --> 00:03:40,457
It's almost since the beginning.

84
00:03:40,977 --> 00:03:43,198
And I'm paid the exact same way as someone

85
00:03:43,218 --> 00:03:44,899
who, say, arrived two years ago.

86
00:03:45,499 --> 00:03:46,719
So it's really important.

87
00:03:46,779 --> 00:03:49,180
It seems like, OK, it's a super hardcore leftist thing.

88
00:03:50,760 --> 00:03:51,540
It is in some way.

89
00:03:51,580 --> 00:03:56,321
But it actually makes hiring people very, very efficient.

90
00:03:56,381 --> 00:03:58,762
Because when you get a newcomer in this company,

91
00:03:59,122 --> 00:04:01,502
he actually gets paid and has the same decision

92
00:04:01,523 --> 00:04:04,063
power as someone else after a test period, of course.

93
00:04:05,303 --> 00:04:08,484
It actually makes people feeling empowered really quickly.

94
00:04:08,904 --> 00:04:11,785
And they are involved much, much more quickly.

95
00:04:12,165 --> 00:04:14,208
than in any kind of class.

96
00:04:14,528 --> 00:04:16,791
So it makes everything, actually, on a day-to-day basis

97
00:04:16,992 --> 00:04:17,893
much easier to do.

98
00:04:19,595 --> 00:04:21,197
Let's talk about dead cells now quickly.

99
00:04:21,938 --> 00:04:24,101
Actually, did someone play dead cells in this room?

100
00:04:26,631 --> 00:04:27,091
Yeah.

101
00:04:27,791 --> 00:04:27,991
OK.

102
00:04:28,491 --> 00:04:29,092
I was stressed.

103
00:04:29,152 --> 00:04:30,092
Now I am terrified.

104
00:04:30,212 --> 00:04:31,112
So it's OK.

105
00:04:31,972 --> 00:04:34,893
So that's basically what we call a rogue Vanya.

106
00:04:35,013 --> 00:04:38,794
It's marketing bullshit, but it actually explains things well.

107
00:04:38,854 --> 00:04:41,275
It's basically Castlevania that you can play again and again.

108
00:04:41,715 --> 00:04:44,055
So every time you die and get back at the beginning,

109
00:04:44,315 --> 00:04:45,976
you have a fresh experience in some way.

110
00:04:46,276 --> 00:04:48,256
The levels are different, but not totally different.

111
00:04:48,617 --> 00:04:50,157
So it's really that, Castlevania, that you

112
00:04:50,177 --> 00:04:51,017
can play again and again.

113
00:04:53,089 --> 00:04:55,310
Oh, you have to know, it was a last chance project.

114
00:04:55,370 --> 00:04:57,331
As I said, we almost died making mobile games.

115
00:04:57,551 --> 00:05:00,192
And by this time, because of the decline of the web,

116
00:05:00,652 --> 00:05:02,393
the company was not in such great shape.

117
00:05:02,453 --> 00:05:05,014
So we had, of course, cash issues and everything.

118
00:05:05,554 --> 00:05:07,295
And at one point, we decided, OK,

119
00:05:07,335 --> 00:05:09,576
do we want to make mobile games forever?

120
00:05:10,536 --> 00:05:11,577
Do we want to do something else?

121
00:05:11,657 --> 00:05:13,219
And at one point, we actually decided,

122
00:05:13,339 --> 00:05:15,501
maybe we should just make a PC title.

123
00:05:15,621 --> 00:05:17,983
Maybe that's the last one, so let's make something big.

124
00:05:18,583 --> 00:05:20,665
And this was actually a good idea,

125
00:05:20,725 --> 00:05:23,247
because luckily, we have survived this.

126
00:05:23,648 --> 00:05:26,070
But it was really, if this project did fail,

127
00:05:26,090 --> 00:05:30,053
I think I would just be today making a sad post-mortem

128
00:05:30,133 --> 00:05:31,755
of how it was cool before.

129
00:05:32,315 --> 00:05:33,897
So no, it's not that today.

130
00:05:34,717 --> 00:05:37,779
We spent about two years and a half making this game.

131
00:05:38,259 --> 00:05:41,360
We spent about one year and a half on the early access thing.

132
00:05:41,841 --> 00:05:44,142
We announced it one year, but we spent a little bit more

133
00:05:44,202 --> 00:05:46,703
because we had tons of interesting feedback.

134
00:05:47,243 --> 00:05:49,124
And we also made the console port,

135
00:05:49,344 --> 00:05:51,605
which was something planned at the beginning.

136
00:05:51,885 --> 00:05:54,286
So it took about six months to make all the free consoles.

137
00:05:54,907 --> 00:05:56,848
And so it was a little bit longer than expected,

138
00:05:56,888 --> 00:05:58,648
but still not too far from what we

139
00:05:58,688 --> 00:06:01,970
announced to players at the beginning, one year and a half.

140
00:06:02,992 --> 00:06:05,652
The game itself sold more than 1 million units, which

141
00:06:05,732 --> 00:06:07,553
is unexpected and cool.

142
00:06:07,953 --> 00:06:09,733
So we are really happy about that, of course.

143
00:06:10,333 --> 00:06:15,234
And about 60% as of today is on PC, which is quite normal

144
00:06:15,294 --> 00:06:17,975
because the PC version, the early access,

145
00:06:18,335 --> 00:06:20,055
went live one year before.

146
00:06:20,435 --> 00:06:23,336
But the thing is, the console is really a big part of it,

147
00:06:23,416 --> 00:06:25,397
and especially the Switch.

148
00:06:25,797 --> 00:06:27,537
So the Switch is a thing today.

149
00:06:27,577 --> 00:06:30,718
So you already know that, so I won't elaborate on this.

150
00:06:32,055 --> 00:06:32,875
So the game itself.

151
00:06:33,916 --> 00:06:35,778
The game is based on three pillars.

152
00:06:37,299 --> 00:06:38,880
The first one is obviously combat.

153
00:06:39,041 --> 00:06:41,643
This game is all about killing stuff and not

154
00:06:41,683 --> 00:06:44,325
trying to get killed, or trying not to get killed, of course.

155
00:06:44,986 --> 00:06:47,508
And so really all about that, positioning in space,

156
00:06:47,548 --> 00:06:50,590
avoiding attacks, reading patterns, and killing enemies.

157
00:06:51,231 --> 00:06:52,372
It's also about progression.

158
00:06:53,453 --> 00:06:55,234
We wanted to have a strong sense of progression.

159
00:06:55,535 --> 00:06:57,056
That's a free-to-play legacy, something

160
00:06:57,096 --> 00:06:58,097
that we wanted to carry on.

161
00:06:58,837 --> 00:07:01,759
And also it's all about replayability, also something

162
00:07:01,799 --> 00:07:04,040
that came for us from the free-to-play,

163
00:07:04,320 --> 00:07:05,281
the way free-to-play before.

164
00:07:05,721 --> 00:07:09,363
We have always been making games that you can

165
00:07:09,403 --> 00:07:11,004
play for hundreds of hours.

166
00:07:11,024 --> 00:07:12,284
So we wanted to have something like that.

167
00:07:13,005 --> 00:07:14,786
But all these three aspects are nothing

168
00:07:14,946 --> 00:07:17,827
compared to one very important thing, which is,

169
00:07:17,847 --> 00:07:19,548
oh, the parameters.

170
00:07:20,354 --> 00:07:22,975
You know, permadeath is like the old thing

171
00:07:22,995 --> 00:07:25,336
that everyone wants in the game, but no one wants in the game.

172
00:07:25,856 --> 00:07:29,477
And when we decided to make a permadeath-oriented game,

173
00:07:29,897 --> 00:07:32,578
it actually made lots of things.

174
00:07:33,859 --> 00:07:35,719
It changed lots of things in the game.

175
00:07:36,619 --> 00:07:37,000
So yeah.

176
00:07:38,481 --> 00:07:41,284
Making a permadeath game is all about embracing this idea.

177
00:07:41,324 --> 00:07:43,005
OK, you're going to kill the player.

178
00:07:43,045 --> 00:07:43,766
You will be sad.

179
00:07:43,806 --> 00:07:45,608
You will have to start naked at the beginning.

180
00:07:45,708 --> 00:07:47,950
So you have to make sure that it's actually a good experience,

181
00:07:48,050 --> 00:07:49,932
which on the paper doesn't seem like one.

182
00:07:50,232 --> 00:07:51,814
But anyway, we'll try to do that.

183
00:07:52,715 --> 00:07:56,759
So internally, permadeath was obviously a very hot topic.

184
00:07:56,799 --> 00:07:58,781
Actually, at one point, we were not

185
00:07:58,821 --> 00:08:00,783
sure if we wanted to make a permadeath game.

186
00:08:01,163 --> 00:08:03,964
So it could have been more classic Castlevania type

187
00:08:04,004 --> 00:08:04,324
of game.

188
00:08:04,724 --> 00:08:06,184
But because we were a small company,

189
00:08:06,204 --> 00:08:10,626
it was not possible for us to make like a 15 hours long title

190
00:08:10,946 --> 00:08:12,606
with tons of unique content.

191
00:08:12,626 --> 00:08:14,967
That was not something because we were just eight people.

192
00:08:15,347 --> 00:08:17,588
And at the beginning, we just had one graphic artist

193
00:08:17,628 --> 00:08:22,969
to make everything at 1.02, which was, wow, more.

194
00:08:23,149 --> 00:08:25,390
So it was definitely not possible to make a single,

195
00:08:25,730 --> 00:08:27,290
not permadeath game for us.

196
00:08:28,566 --> 00:08:31,928
So at one point, someone had this idea of maybe we

197
00:08:32,368 --> 00:08:35,750
should make the death as part of the progression in this game.

198
00:08:35,770 --> 00:08:38,352
Maybe we should consider that dying should be like,

199
00:08:38,552 --> 00:08:40,533
oh, yeah, I died, so I can do something new.

200
00:08:41,114 --> 00:08:42,915
And this actually defined lots of stuff.

201
00:08:42,935 --> 00:08:46,397
This was a really great idea, great internal idea

202
00:08:46,417 --> 00:08:46,777
that we had.

203
00:08:47,637 --> 00:08:50,179
Not to brag here, but yes, it changed really everything.

204
00:08:50,499 --> 00:08:53,220
First thing that was changed was we

205
00:08:53,440 --> 00:08:55,461
don't have any kind of backtracking between levels.

206
00:08:55,881 --> 00:08:58,101
So it means, for example, if you start the first level, which

207
00:08:58,161 --> 00:09:00,482
is a prison, if you exit this level

208
00:09:00,502 --> 00:09:02,223
and go to the promenade, which is the second one,

209
00:09:02,583 --> 00:09:03,903
you cannot go back to the prison.

210
00:09:03,983 --> 00:09:05,464
And if you want to play against the prison,

211
00:09:05,484 --> 00:09:07,964
you actually have to die to get back at the beginning again.

212
00:09:08,384 --> 00:09:10,105
So you cannot get back between levels.

213
00:09:10,125 --> 00:09:12,006
You can do whatever you want in a single level,

214
00:09:12,126 --> 00:09:13,286
but no backtracking.

215
00:09:15,087 --> 00:09:18,629
Another aspect is making sure that each run counts

216
00:09:19,029 --> 00:09:19,430
in some way.

217
00:09:20,390 --> 00:09:23,292
The way we did that is using the so-called dead cells

218
00:09:23,392 --> 00:09:23,912
in this game.

219
00:09:23,992 --> 00:09:26,393
When you kill someone, you probably

220
00:09:26,413 --> 00:09:29,335
will get dead cells, the blue dead cells.

221
00:09:29,775 --> 00:09:31,936
These dead cells can be used in a shop

222
00:09:32,076 --> 00:09:33,717
that you will see from time to time, which

223
00:09:33,777 --> 00:09:34,578
is called the collector.

224
00:09:35,238 --> 00:09:38,660
And this shop allows you to invest your cells

225
00:09:39,260 --> 00:09:41,462
and to actually make progress on something,

226
00:09:41,862 --> 00:09:44,923
such as unlocking a new weapon, a new skill, or whatever.

227
00:09:46,440 --> 00:09:47,740
It's really about investing sales.

228
00:09:47,880 --> 00:09:49,821
The thing is, if you die, you lose your sales.

229
00:09:50,261 --> 00:09:52,142
But if you die, you keep this progress.

230
00:09:52,543 --> 00:09:57,225
So it's really your goal is basically to get that sales, invest them so they are stuck

231
00:09:57,425 --> 00:09:57,865
in this bar.

232
00:09:58,125 --> 00:10:00,386
So you actually make progress every time you play.

233
00:10:01,143 --> 00:10:04,145
And at one point, maybe after two or three runs,

234
00:10:04,285 --> 00:10:06,566
you may unlock a weapon or unlock a skill

235
00:10:06,586 --> 00:10:07,887
that you have chosen to invest on.

236
00:10:08,347 --> 00:10:09,768
So it's really all about that, making sure

237
00:10:09,808 --> 00:10:12,650
that your death on this run wasn't useless.

238
00:10:12,790 --> 00:10:14,551
At least you make some progress on something,

239
00:10:14,651 --> 00:10:16,072
and maybe you have unlocked something.

240
00:10:18,133 --> 00:10:21,275
And also we do have, you know, it's still castle vanish thing.

241
00:10:21,415 --> 00:10:24,577
So we do have metroid vanish things in this game.

242
00:10:24,637 --> 00:10:25,338
So for example.

243
00:10:26,367 --> 00:10:28,589
This is a basic world map of the game at the beginning.

244
00:10:28,609 --> 00:10:30,831
So you just start on the left in the prison, the first level,

245
00:10:31,292 --> 00:10:33,994
and then you move to the promenade.

246
00:10:34,435 --> 00:10:36,517
And after that, you go to the ramparts, and you have a boss,

247
00:10:36,577 --> 00:10:38,378
and so on, and you continue through the game.

248
00:10:38,939 --> 00:10:41,581
But at one point, in the second level, in the promenade,

249
00:10:42,022 --> 00:10:44,123
you will get a new skill, which is permanent.

250
00:10:44,303 --> 00:10:47,265
And this skill allows you to grow vines out of the ground

251
00:10:47,365 --> 00:10:51,007
and to build ladders at specific points that

252
00:10:51,067 --> 00:10:53,309
were before that unreachable.

253
00:10:53,709 --> 00:10:55,230
It's like an extra ladder that you

254
00:10:55,270 --> 00:10:57,631
can build in specific places.

