526
00:21:30,341 --> 00:21:31,962
It has splash damage, something that we

527
00:21:32,002 --> 00:21:33,543
added which was really hidden.

528
00:21:33,583 --> 00:21:35,104
But it feels intuitive.

529
00:21:35,204 --> 00:21:36,825
If you have an enemy falling on another one,

530
00:21:36,845 --> 00:21:38,667
it actually takes lots of damage from that.

531
00:21:39,247 --> 00:21:42,689
So you see this sequence is actually maybe five seconds

532
00:21:42,809 --> 00:21:44,010
long in real time.

533
00:21:44,510 --> 00:21:46,692
And lots is happening inside this sequence.

534
00:21:47,492 --> 00:21:49,974
We don't want jumping to be an issue here.

535
00:21:50,014 --> 00:21:52,375
We don't want the player to actually miss the platform.

536
00:21:52,415 --> 00:21:54,797
So we really teleport him like a lot.

537
00:21:55,237 --> 00:21:59,621
We don't want an attack to miss because there are three more enemies in this room, so we

538
00:21:59,641 --> 00:22:03,024
don't want this single attack to miss, especially because it was a killing blow.

539
00:22:04,165 --> 00:22:07,168
So we have lots of things like this happening, and it's really, really important.

540
00:22:08,417 --> 00:22:11,040
One thing that we actually noticed when we made that,

541
00:22:11,921 --> 00:22:14,604
it actually allowed us for much more difficulty in this game.

542
00:22:14,624 --> 00:22:18,087
It allowed us to make much more difficult combat

543
00:22:18,127 --> 00:22:20,710
and everything, because it was all about strategy and less

544
00:22:20,750 --> 00:22:24,014
about actual controls or platforming or whatever.

545
00:22:24,034 --> 00:22:26,797
It's really all about, yes, thinking what's happening,

546
00:22:26,937 --> 00:22:29,200
what I'm going to do, and thinking split second.

547
00:22:30,382 --> 00:22:32,482
And something that we also discovered,

